(454, '_site_transient_ddwplir-plinfo-customizer-export-import', 'O:8:\"stdClass\":27:{s:4:\"name\";s:24:\"Customizer Export/Import\";s:4:\"slug\";s:24:\"customizer-export-import\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"0.9.2\";s:6:\"author\";s:144:\"<a href=\"http://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/?utm_source=external&utm_medium=customizer-export&utm_campaign=plugins-page\">The Beaver Builder Team</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/justinbusa\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:2:{s:10:\"justinbusa\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/justinbusa\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/cd087cea9ecb1067b23c98deac24a543?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:11:\"Justin Busa\";}s:5:\"pross\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:36:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pross\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/df9c761356c574b3fd5042db3273e438?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:13:\"Simon Prosser\";}}s:8:\"requires\";s:3:\"3.6\";s:6:\"tested\";s:5:\"5.5.1\";s:12:\"requires_php\";b:0;s:6:\"rating\";i:96;s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:78;i:4;i:1;i:3;i:0;i:2;i:0;i:1;i:3;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:82;s:15:\"support_threads\";i:3;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:0;s:15:\"active_installs\";i:200000;s:12:\"last_updated\";s:21:\"2020-08-20 5:07pm GMT\";s:5:\"added\";s:10:\"2014-12-20\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:148:\"http://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/wordpress-customizer-export-import-plugin/?utm_source=external&utm_medium=customizer-export&utm_campaign=plugins-page\";s:8:\"sections\";a:6:{s:11:\"description\";s:3082:\"<h4>Customizer Export/Import</h4>\n<p>The Customizer Export/Import plugin allows you to export or import your WordPress customizer settings from directly within the customizer interface! If your theme makes use of the WordPress customizer for its settings, this plugin is for you!</p>\n<p>Please visit our blog for more info on the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/wordpress-customizer-export-import-plugin/?utm_source=external&amp;utm_medium=wp-repo&amp;utm_campaign=customizer-export-description\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Customizer Export/Import plugin</a>.</p>\n<h4>New! Export Options</h4>\n<p>The Customizer Export/Import plugin previously only exported options saved as theme mods using the <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/get_theme_mods\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">get_theme_mods</a> function, but that is no more! The Customizer Export/Import plugin now exports settings saved as options as well!</p>\n<h4>How It Works</h4>\n<p>Exporting customizer settings is easy. Click the export button from within the customizer and a file will automatically begin downloading with your settings. Export files are named after your theme and can only be used to import settings for the theme or child theme that they came from. Export files contain a serialized dump of mods retrieved using the <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/get_theme_mods\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">get_theme_mods</a> function or customizer settings saved as options.</p>\n<p>Importing customizer settings is just as easy. Choose the export file you would like to import, select whether you would like to download and import images (similar to importing posts), and finally, click the import button. Once your settings have been imported the page will refresh and your new design will be displayed.</p>\n<h4>Exporting Custom Options</h4>\n<p>Developers can also have arbitrary options that aren&rsquo;t part of the customizer exported by using the cei_export_option_keys filter. Those options can be exported and imported by adding your option key to the array of options that will be exported as shown below.</p>\n<pre><code>function my_export_option_keys( $keys ) {\n    $keys[] = \'my_option_key\';\n    $keys[] = \'another_option_key\';\n    return $keys;\n}\n\nadd_filter( \'cei_export_option_keys\', \'my_export_option_keys\' );\n</code></pre>\n<h4>Known Issues</h4>\n<p>This plugin currently only works for active themes, not themes that are being previewed with either the Theme Test Drive plugin or the new customizer theme preview.</p>\n<h4>Contribute!</h4>\n<p>We&rsquo;d love to hear your feedback as to how we could improve the Customizer Export/Import plugin, or better yet, see theme developers actively contribute! Don&rsquo;t hesitate to let us know if you&rsquo;re interested in contributing as we would gladly have others on board.</p>\n<p>The Customizer Export/Import plugin is brought to you by the fine folks at <a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/?utm_source=external&amp;utm_medium=wp-repo&amp;utm_campaign=customizer-export-description\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Beaver Builder</a>.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:321:\"<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install the Customizer Export/Import plugin either via the WordPress plugin directory, or by uploading the files to your server at wp-content/plugins.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>After activating, the export/import functionality will be available as a separate section within the WordPress customizer.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:273:\"<p>Please visit our blog for more info on the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/wordpress-customizer-export-import-plugin/?utm_source=external&amp;utm_medium=wp-repo&amp;utm_campaign=customizer-export-faq\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Customizer Export/Import plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:909:\"<h4>Version 0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Version initiale.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added cei_export_option_keys filter for exporting custom options.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Customizer settings saved as options are now exported and imported.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.5</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed an issue with uploads in WordPress 4.7.1.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.6</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Trying another fix for the issue with uploads in WordPress 4.7.1.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.7</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added support for exporting and importing custom CSS.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.8</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added support for option data that has an empty value.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.9</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Allow options with <code>widget</code> or <code>sidebar</code> in their key to be exported.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 0.9.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed issue with slashes in plugin asset urls and S3. Props Huskynarr.</li>\n</ul>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:287:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/customizer-export-import/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=1049984\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/customizer-export-import/assets/screenshot-1.jpg?rev=1049984\" alt=\"The export/import customizer section.\"></a><p>The export/import customizer section.</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:13676:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">best plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/amrinders698\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5316488d7041c2dc98ebc4a39ba9ee5e?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5316488d7041c2dc98ebc4a39ba9ee5e?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/amrinders698\" class=\"reviewer-name\">amrinders698</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">juillet 10, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">best plugin works great with 5.4.2</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Too bad it&#039;s not still updated. That said, it works fine with latest wordpress.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/markob17\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/88302debe6d0fec89732aea9da0234be?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/88302debe6d0fec89732aea9da0234be?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/markob17\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Mark <small>(markob17)</small></a> le <span class=\"review-date\">juin 15, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">This plugin saved me a lot of time. Not sure if dev is still supporting it, though. That said, it\'s working so maybe no need for an update, idk. </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Perfect!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-fil